Harley-Davidson: A Pictorial Celebration
Motorbooks International | 1993 | 1855322412 | English | 164 pages | PDF | 33 MB

This fascinating books celebrates the multi-faceted world of Harley-Davidson, as author Malcolm Birkitt shows how much Harley-Davidson ownership means to a modern generation that rides for pleasure. Accountants, dentists, teachers, ministers, members of the armed forces, and even police officers in their leisure time take to the open highway on their two-wheel American thoroughbreds
